WEBVTT

00:08.800 --> 00:10.802
[electrical humming]

00:11.177 --> 00:13.555
[breathing masks hissing]

00:20.729 --> 00:21.771
[beeping]

00:27.736 --> 00:28.820
[ringing]

00:28.903 --> 00:30.989
[alarm wailing]

00:46.379 --> 00:47.589
[sighs deeply]

01:22.499 --> 01:25.126
[device powering up]

02:17.470 --> 02:19.556
[creatures squealing]

02:31.025 --> 02:32.902
[rattling sound]

02:59.304 --> 03:03.558
[powering down]

03:12.400 --> 03:14.527
[man screams]

03:59.405 --> 04:00.740
[man, in Russian] Comrade-General.

04:03.451 --> 04:04.994
We are close.

04:05.495 --> 04:06.663
You can see.

04:06.913 --> 04:08.831
You can see our progress.

04:08.915 --> 04:10.375
We just need more ti--

04:10.458 --> 04:12.168
[gasps, chokes]

04:18.132 --> 04:19.092
[choking continues]

04:19.175 --> 04:21.886
[Russian choral song playing]

04:24.514 --> 04:25.723
[in Russian] You have one year.

04:28.518 --> 04:30.436
[in Russian] Yes, Comrade-General.

05:07.598 --> 05:09.892
[theme music playing]

06:07.033 --> 06:12.580
♪ Just a little more time
Is all we're asking for ♪

06:15.958 --> 06:22.340
♪ 'Cause just a little more time
Could open closing doors ♪

06:25.468 --> 06:31.474
♪ Just a little uncertainty
Can bring you down ♪

06:34.811 --> 06:38.439
[singing along]
♪ And nobody wants to know you now ♪

06:38.523 --> 06:39.649
[imitates guitar break]

06:39.732 --> 06:41.776
-♪   Nobody wants to show you--  ♪
-Mike!

06:41.859 --> 06:43.945
Mike, stop! Stop!

06:44.028 --> 06:47.990
-♪  So if you're lost and on your own  ♪
-Mike! Stop!

06:48.074 --> 06:49.242
Mike! Mike!

06:49.325 --> 06:52.537
-♪  You can never surrender  ♪
-[laughing] Stop!

06:54.122 --> 06:56.332
-What, you don't like it?
-No!

06:57.500 --> 06:58.835
[Eleven laughs]

07:00.294 --> 07:02.630
[man on TV]  Don't look at the dogs,
work the lock.

07:03.339 --> 07:05.925
Work the lock. Work the lock.
Don't look at the dogs.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.718
You looked at the dogs.

07:10.179 --> 07:11.305
[dogs barking on TV]

07:11.389 --> 07:14.016
Sometimes everything goes
exactly as planned.

07:15.601 --> 07:16.769
[burps]

07:18.771 --> 07:20.148
[chair creaks]

07:27.780 --> 07:28.948
Hey!

07:29.949 --> 07:31.075
Hey!

07:32.076 --> 07:33.536
Three-inch minimum!

07:33.703 --> 07:35.580
Leave the door open three inches!

07:36.497 --> 07:37.623
[rattles doorknob]

07:38.875 --> 07:40.918
El, open this door.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.129
Open the--

07:46.215 --> 07:47.049
What's wrong?

07:52.889 --> 07:54.682
[Mike] My God, that was priceless!

07:54.891 --> 07:56.142
Did you see his face?

07:56.225 --> 07:58.269
[panting] It was like a tomato!

07:58.895 --> 08:00.271
Yeah, a fat tomato.

08:00.354 --> 08:03.065
-I wish I was still with you.
-I know.

08:03.149 --> 08:04.066
Me too.

08:04.150 --> 08:06.360
But I'll see you tomorrow, all right?
First thing.

08:06.444 --> 08:07.570
Tomorrow.

08:11.949 --> 08:13.951
[upbeat synth music playing]

08:25.505 --> 08:26.589
-You're late.
-[Mike] Sorry!

08:26.672 --> 08:28.132
-Again.
-We're gonna miss the opening.

08:28.216 --> 08:30.176
Yeah, if you keeping whining
about it. Let's go!

08:30.259 --> 08:32.428
"If you guys keep whining about it.
Nyeh-nyeh-nyeh."

08:32.512 --> 08:34.597
-[Mike] Just please stop talking, dude.
-Let me guess.

08:34.680 --> 08:35.973
You were busy. [smacks lips]

08:36.057 --> 08:37.600
Oh, yeah, real mature, Lucas.

08:37.683 --> 08:39.727
"Oh, El, I wish we could make out forever,

08:39.810 --> 08:41.646
and never hang out
with any of our friends."

08:41.729 --> 08:42.897
Lucas, stop.

08:42.980 --> 08:44.565
-Will thinks it's funny.
-Because it is.

08:44.649 --> 08:47.568
Yeah, it's so funny that I want to spend
romantic time with my girlfriend.

08:47.652 --> 08:49.820
[Lucas] I'm spending romantic time
with my girlfriend.

08:53.032 --> 08:55.326
-[girl] Hey!
-Excuse us! Sorry! Sorry!

08:55.409 --> 08:57.620
Sorry, sorry, sorry!

08:57.828 --> 08:59.539
-[Max] Excuse me, I'm sorry.
-[Will] Sorry.

08:59.872 --> 09:01.082
-Hey!
-Watch it!

09:01.165 --> 09:03.167
Yeah! Watch it, nerd!

09:03.251 --> 09:04.544
Isn't it past your bedtime?

09:04.627 --> 09:06.087
Isn't it time you died?

09:06.170 --> 09:07.922
-Psycho!
-Butthead!

09:08.005 --> 09:09.465
-Mall rat!
-Fart face!

09:09.549 --> 09:11.551
-[blows raspberry]
-Oh, now that was mature.

09:17.181 --> 09:18.724
[rings bell repeatedly]

09:18.808 --> 09:20.810
Hey, dingus, your children are here.

09:22.395 --> 09:24.230
Again? Seriously?

09:25.648 --> 09:26.524
[bell rings]

09:30.278 --> 09:31.112
Come on, come on.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.198
I swear, if anybody hears about this--

09:34.282 --> 09:35.283
[all] We're dead!

09:37.660 --> 09:38.911
[sighs]

09:42.582 --> 09:43.499
All clear.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.585
[pre-movie jingle playing]

09:49.130 --> 09:51.632
[movie fanfare playing]

09:56.804 --> 09:58.681
[funk music playing]

10:03.144 --> 10:04.103
See, Lucas? We made it.

10:04.186 --> 10:06.731
-We missed the previews.
-Still made it. Fart face.

10:07.231 --> 10:08.190
Shh.

10:17.074 --> 10:18.326
-[Lucas] Skittles.
-[Max] Thanks.

10:32.298 --> 10:33.716
[audio slows, stops]

10:33.799 --> 10:35.259
[crowd clamors]

10:35.343 --> 10:37.261
-Come on!
-Come on!

10:39.639 --> 10:41.515
[carnival music slows, stops]

10:42.308 --> 10:43.351
[all gasp]

10:44.560 --> 10:45.394
The hell?

10:47.438 --> 10:48.272
[Steve] That's weird.

10:54.987 --> 10:56.364
That isn't gonna work, dingus.

10:56.447 --> 10:57.448
Oh, really?

11:34.151 --> 11:35.611
[rats squealing]

11:55.715 --> 11:57.216
[frantic squealing]

12:00.469 --> 12:01.595
[distorted roaring]

12:03.055 --> 12:04.181
[scattered cheering]

12:06.600 --> 12:07.727
[carnival music resumes]

12:07.810 --> 12:09.311
[laughing]

12:12.440 --> 12:13.566
[nautical tune playing]

12:14.358 --> 12:15.443
Let there be light.

12:17.653 --> 12:19.196
[film reel sputtering]

12:19.989 --> 12:21.991
[cheering]

12:22.074 --> 12:24.076
[movie soundtrack resumes]

12:30.875 --> 12:32.334
[cheering continues]

12:32.418 --> 12:34.795
[fluttering sound]

12:34.879 --> 12:36.422
[low growling]

12:36.505 --> 12:38.507
[cheering fades]

12:39.592 --> 12:42.762
[creature roaring]

12:46.307 --> 12:47.850
[screaming]

12:49.727 --> 12:50.644
-Hey.
-[gasps]

12:51.896 --> 12:52.813
You okay?

12:53.355 --> 12:54.190
Yeah.

12:54.899 --> 12:55.733
Are you sure?

12:57.276 --> 12:58.110
Of course.

12:59.320 --> 13:00.196
Okay.

13:11.040 --> 13:11.957
[crowd gasps]

13:12.750 --> 13:13.584
Shit!

13:14.251 --> 13:15.085
[gasps]

13:15.711 --> 13:17.171
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit!

13:17.254 --> 13:19.089
-Wh-- What's wrong?
-It's almost 9:00.

13:19.173 --> 13:21.050
-What?
-We forgot to reset the clocks.

13:21.133 --> 13:23.552
-The power went out last night, remember?
-Oh, shit!

13:24.553 --> 13:26.013
["Open the Door" playing]

13:29.225 --> 13:30.142
Whoa! [grunts]

13:34.230 --> 13:36.232
♪ Come on with a gun ♪

13:36.857 --> 13:39.235
♪ Come on with a heart attack... ♪

13:39.318 --> 13:40.361
Hey, hey, hey!

13:40.444 --> 13:42.363
-Wait up.
-Oh, no, I'll eat at work.

13:42.446 --> 13:43.322
-I'm late.
-No.

13:43.405 --> 13:45.366
-Your cheek.
-All right, all right.

13:45.616 --> 13:47.827
-I gotta run. See you later.
-All right.

13:48.911 --> 13:50.496
Ugh. Gross.

13:50.579 --> 13:54.083
Well, I don't think you're gonna think
it's gross when you fall in love.

13:54.166 --> 13:56.335
I'm not gonna fall in love.

13:56.418 --> 13:57.253
Okay.

14:00.214 --> 14:01.048
Hey.

14:01.924 --> 14:03.008
What happened here?

14:03.217 --> 14:04.093
I don't know.

14:05.052 --> 14:07.388
♪ Love that was new to you ♪

14:07.638 --> 14:10.140
♪ You open up the door ♪

14:10.224 --> 14:12.726
♪ I fall below my feet ♪

14:12.810 --> 14:17.815
♪ I crawl out on the floor ♪

14:24.488 --> 14:25.906
[Nancy] Can you please drive faster?

14:25.990 --> 14:28.868
Do you wanna break down? We're lucky
this thing still drives at all.

14:28.951 --> 14:30.828
I'm serious, Jonathan, I can't be late.

14:30.911 --> 14:33.747
-You mean  we  can't be late.
-No, I mean I can't be late.

14:33.831 --> 14:36.542
-They like you no matter what you do.
-Hey, they like you too.

14:36.625 --> 14:39.712
Yeah. They like that I'm
a coffee delivery machine.

14:39.795 --> 14:41.755
They don't actually like me
or respect me

14:41.839 --> 14:44.550
as a living, breathing human
with a brain.

14:44.633 --> 14:47.386
Wait, you just--
you just gotta be patient, okay?

14:47.469 --> 14:49.179
They're set in their ways, you know?

14:49.263 --> 14:51.473
But... once they realize
what a gifted writer you are,

14:51.557 --> 14:52.391
they'll come around.

14:52.474 --> 14:54.935
I really don't need a Jonathan Byers
pep talk right now.

14:55.227 --> 14:57.354
Can you just... please drive faster?

14:57.980 --> 14:58.856
Okay.

15:06.947 --> 15:09.867
[Dustin] This is Gold Leader,
returning to base. Do you copy? Over.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.954
This is Gold Leader, returning to base.
Do you copy? Over.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.790
I repeat: This is Gold Leader,

15:16.874 --> 15:19.335
returning to base. Do you copy? Over.

15:19.418 --> 15:22.254
-I repeat: This is goddamn Gold Leader--
-Dusty!

15:22.338 --> 15:24.965
-What?
-Relax! For goodness' sake.

15:25.049 --> 15:26.884
I'm in range. They should be answering.

15:26.967 --> 15:29.261
You've been away a whole month,
honeybun. Maybe they just...

15:29.345 --> 15:30.804
forgot.

15:33.432 --> 15:35.809
♪ You open up the door ♪

15:36.310 --> 15:38.520
♪ I fall below my feet ♪

15:38.604 --> 15:42.316
♪ I crawl out on the floor... ♪

15:51.325 --> 15:52.576
[sighs]

15:55.704 --> 15:56.580
[Dustin chuckles]

15:56.664 --> 15:58.666
At least someone's happy I'm home.

16:00.167 --> 16:01.669
[distorted robotic whirring]

16:05.255 --> 16:07.591
[beeping]

16:09.385 --> 16:11.345
[cymbal crashing]

16:13.555 --> 16:15.265
[zapping]

16:15.349 --> 16:16.976
[sound of gunfire]

16:23.232 --> 16:24.191
[train whistle blows]

16:38.998 --> 16:40.290
[Dustin] It's just a dream.

16:41.333 --> 16:42.209
You're dreaming.

16:45.379 --> 16:47.381
[cacophony of toy sounds continues]

16:54.888 --> 16:55.848
[whispers] Now!

16:55.931 --> 16:57.141
[toys power down]

17:07.026 --> 17:08.569
-[noisemakers sounding]
-[screams]

17:08.652 --> 17:11.030
[both scream]

17:12.114 --> 17:14.366
[yells] Cannonball!

17:15.242 --> 17:16.869
["Rock This Town" playing]

17:16.952 --> 17:18.328
♪ We're gonna rock this town ♪

17:18.412 --> 17:20.456
♪ Make 'em scream and shout... ♪

17:22.541 --> 17:23.876
[girl yells] Marco!

17:23.959 --> 17:25.502
[group of kids] Polo!

17:25.586 --> 17:26.920
[girl] Marco!

17:27.004 --> 17:28.047
[kids] Polo!

17:28.130 --> 17:29.298
[girl] Marco!

17:29.381 --> 17:30.466
[kids] Polo!

17:30.549 --> 17:31.717
[girl] Marco!

17:31.800 --> 17:32.885
[kids] Polo!

17:32.968 --> 17:34.136
[girl] Marco!

17:34.219 --> 17:35.304
[kids] Polo!

17:36.597 --> 17:37.931
♪  We're gonna rock this town  ♪

17:38.015 --> 17:41.477
♪  Rock it inside out  ♪

17:42.478 --> 17:43.312
Ladies.

17:44.521 --> 17:45.689
She's coming down.

17:45.773 --> 17:47.941
["Moving in Stereo" playing]

18:00.329 --> 18:02.372
And... showtime.

18:15.761 --> 18:17.096
♪ Life's the same ♪

18:17.179 --> 18:19.765
♪ I'm moving in stereo ♪

18:19.848 --> 18:21.475
♪ Life's the same ♪

18:21.558 --> 18:23.477
♪ Except for my shoes ♪

18:24.019 --> 18:25.354
♪ Life's the same ♪

18:25.437 --> 18:27.356
♪ You're shakin' like tremolo ♪

18:28.148 --> 18:29.566
♪ Life's the same ♪

18:29.650 --> 18:33.695
♪ It's all inside you ♪

18:35.405 --> 18:36.240
[blows whistle]

18:36.990 --> 18:37.908
[whistle blowing]

18:39.243 --> 18:40.285
Hey, lard-ass!

18:40.369 --> 18:41.203
[crowd quietens]

18:41.286 --> 18:42.830
No running on my watch!

18:42.996 --> 18:45.332
I gotta warn you again,
and you're banned for life.

18:45.415 --> 18:47.209
You wanna be banned for life, lard-ass?

18:48.293 --> 18:49.336
Didn't think so.

18:50.337 --> 18:51.171
[blows whistle]

18:51.255 --> 18:52.631
[crowd chatter resumes]

18:54.675 --> 18:55.717
Afternoon, ladies.

18:55.801 --> 18:57.302
[in unison] Afternoon, Billy.

18:57.845 --> 18:59.179
Dig the new suit, Mrs. Wheeler.

18:59.263 --> 19:00.514
Thank you.

19:20.117 --> 19:22.119
[wind whistling]

19:35.382 --> 19:36.216
[door bell jingles]

19:37.384 --> 19:38.427
-Hey.
-Hey.

19:38.886 --> 19:39.761
You busy?

19:40.345 --> 19:42.055
You're our first customer, so...

19:44.766 --> 19:46.226
[scoffs] What now?

19:47.519 --> 19:50.647
And then El, she just... slams the door.

19:50.731 --> 19:51.899
Right in my face.

19:51.982 --> 19:53.108
Uh-huh?

19:53.275 --> 19:56.236
You know, it is that smug
son of a bitch, Mike.

19:56.320 --> 19:58.238
He's corrupting her, I'm telling you.

19:58.322 --> 20:00.866
And I'm just gonna lose it.
I mean, I am gonna lose it, Joyce.

20:00.949 --> 20:02.910
Just take it down, Hopper.

20:02.993 --> 20:04.494
I need for them to break up.

20:04.578 --> 20:06.163
That is not your decision.

20:06.246 --> 20:09.708
They're spending entirely too much
time together.

20:10.417 --> 20:12.002
You agree with me about that, right?

20:12.085 --> 20:14.963
Well, I mean, they're just kissing, right?

20:15.547 --> 20:17.758
Yeah, but it is constant.

20:17.841 --> 20:20.135
It is constant.

20:20.219 --> 20:23.013
Okay? That is not normal,

20:23.180 --> 20:24.640
that is not healthy.

20:24.723 --> 20:27.351
You can't just force them apart.

20:27.517 --> 20:29.645
I mean,
they're not little kids anymore, Hop.

20:29.728 --> 20:30.896
They're teenagers.

20:30.979 --> 20:33.482
If you order them around like a cop,
then they're gonna rebel.

20:33.565 --> 20:34.900
It's just what they do.

20:34.983 --> 20:37.486
So what, I'm just supposed to
let them do whatever they want?

20:37.569 --> 20:40.656
No, I didn't say that.
I think you should... talk to them.

20:40.739 --> 20:43.075
No. No. 'Cause talking doesn't work.

20:43.158 --> 20:45.744
Not yelling. Not ordering.

20:45.827 --> 20:47.454
But talk to them.

20:48.247 --> 20:49.957
You know, like a heart-to-heart.

20:51.708 --> 20:52.960
A heart-to-heart?

20:53.877 --> 20:54.711
What is that?

20:54.795 --> 20:58.382
You sit them down and you talk to them,
like you're their friend.

20:58.465 --> 21:01.218
I find if you talk to them
like you're on their level,

21:01.301 --> 21:02.803
then they really start to listen.

21:02.886 --> 21:05.347
And then, you know,
you could start to create some boundaries.

21:06.306 --> 21:07.891
-Boundaries.
-Yeah, but,

21:07.975 --> 21:11.812
Hop, it's really important
that no matter how they respond,

21:11.937 --> 21:13.063
you stay calm.

21:13.146 --> 21:15.399
You cannot lose your temper.

21:16.316 --> 21:17.442
Uh...

21:17.818 --> 21:19.861
Maybe you could do it for me?

21:19.945 --> 21:21.113
No.

21:21.196 --> 21:23.490
Yeah, you could. Yeah, you could.
You come over after work.

21:23.573 --> 21:25.033
-Yes.
-No.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.703
It only works if it comes from you.

21:29.454 --> 21:30.289
But...

21:31.081 --> 21:34.042
-But?
-Maybe I can help you...

21:34.501 --> 21:36.670
find the right words.

21:41.174 --> 21:43.260
["Workin' For a Livin'" playing]

21:46.388 --> 21:47.723
♪  Ooh, whoa! ♪

21:48.473 --> 21:51.143
♪ Some days won't end ever
And some days pass on by ♪

21:51.226 --> 21:52.894
♪ I'll be workin' here forever... ♪

21:53.395 --> 21:54.563
-Thanks, hon.
-For you.

21:55.981 --> 21:56.898
For you.

21:57.316 --> 21:58.900
-[woman] Thanks.
-Welcome.

22:01.486 --> 22:03.196
Oh, no, no, no, no! Nancy!

22:03.864 --> 22:05.032
Sorry.

22:09.161 --> 22:12.122
-[man 1] How 'bout a piece on Iran?
-[man 2] I want something local.

22:12.205 --> 22:14.583
I hear there's a beauty pageant
at the fair this year.

22:14.666 --> 22:17.210
Yeah, I'm looking for above the fold here,
Bruce.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.171
Then clearly you haven't seen
Lucy Lebrock,

22:19.254 --> 22:21.590
because I'm not sure she'll fit
above the fold!

22:21.673 --> 22:22.924
[men laughing]

22:23.008 --> 22:23.884
Fellas!

22:23.967 --> 22:26.219
In six hours, we go to print.
I need something real.

22:26.303 --> 22:27.637
Oh, I think they're real.

22:27.721 --> 22:29.931
[men laughing]

22:30.515 --> 22:31.808
What about Starcourt?

22:35.812 --> 22:37.022
I-- I was just...

22:37.105 --> 22:37.981
thinking...

22:38.815 --> 22:40.859
I mean, I know everyone
loves the mall, but...

22:40.942 --> 22:43.362
how many small businesses have closed
since it opened?

22:44.154 --> 22:46.490
Like, five on Main, at least.

22:46.698 --> 22:48.658
It's changing the fabric of our town

22:48.742 --> 22:51.912
-in a way--
-"The Death of Small-Town America."

22:51.995 --> 22:52.913
I like it.

22:52.996 --> 22:54.289
I like it a lot.

22:54.998 --> 22:57.501
But I think I've got something
even spicier.

22:57.584 --> 23:01.880
It's about the missing mustard
on my hamburger.

23:01.963 --> 23:04.591
[men laughing]

23:05.133 --> 23:06.593
You think you can follow the clues

23:06.676 --> 23:09.429
and solve the case
of the missing condiment, Nancy Drew?

23:10.931 --> 23:11.848
Sorry.

23:14.893 --> 23:17.604
Look out, Phil,
she might be after your job!

23:18.230 --> 23:20.065
Ow, ow, ow. Ow.

23:20.148 --> 23:21.358
[groans]

23:21.441 --> 23:22.401
Better?

23:22.484 --> 23:23.902
Still stings.

23:27.656 --> 23:28.490
Is that a new zit?

23:30.033 --> 23:31.034
What is wrong with you?

23:31.118 --> 23:32.994
I was just asking! [screams]

23:33.578 --> 23:35.330
I call it... the Forever Clock.

23:35.914 --> 23:39.334
All right? Powered by wind.
Very useful in the apocalypse.

23:41.002 --> 23:43.004
Then, I give you...

23:43.088 --> 23:44.589
the Slammer.

23:47.968 --> 23:49.928
[chuckles] Pretty neat, huh?

23:50.011 --> 23:51.096
But this...

23:51.513 --> 23:53.390
this is my masterpiece.

23:53.473 --> 23:54.433
[Dustin grunts]

23:55.892 --> 23:58.437
I would like you to meet...

23:59.312 --> 24:00.147
Cerebro.

24:02.023 --> 24:04.067
What exactly are we looking at here?

24:04.151 --> 24:07.737
An unassembled one-of-a-kind
battery-powered radio tower.

24:09.322 --> 24:11.867
So, it's a... a ham radio.

24:12.367 --> 24:14.369
The Cadillac of ham radios.

24:14.453 --> 24:16.455
This baby carries
a crystal-clear connection

24:16.538 --> 24:17.497
over vast distances.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.583
I'm talking North Pole to South.

24:20.417 --> 24:23.462
I can talk to my girlfriend
whenever and wherever I choose.

24:24.379 --> 24:25.297
[all] Girlfriend?

24:26.673 --> 24:28.258
[Mike]  Wait, so her name is Suzie?

24:28.341 --> 24:30.260
Suzie with a "z." She's from Utah.

24:30.343 --> 24:31.595
[Will] Girls go to science camp?

24:31.678 --> 24:33.972
-Suzie does. She's a genius.
-Is she cute?

24:34.055 --> 24:36.183
Think Phoebe Cates, only hotter.

24:36.266 --> 24:38.685
-What's going on?
-Going to talk to Dustin's girlfriend.

24:38.768 --> 24:40.145
[both] Girlfriend?

24:40.729 --> 24:41.813
[door closes]

24:42.439 --> 24:43.648
[nautical tune playing]

24:43.732 --> 24:46.735
Alrighty, one scoop of chocolate.
That's a buck-twenty-five.

24:47.360 --> 24:48.278
Anything else?

24:49.321 --> 24:51.156
Ooh, Purdue.

24:51.448 --> 24:53.366
-Fancy.
-Yeah, I'm excited.

24:54.201 --> 24:55.118
[girls chuckle]

24:55.202 --> 24:57.454
Yeah, you know, I considered it,

24:57.746 --> 24:59.706
Purdue, but then I was like,
you know what?

24:59.831 --> 25:02.792
I really think I need some real-life
experience, you know,

25:02.876 --> 25:05.170
before I hit college,
see what it feels like.

25:05.253 --> 25:06.671
Kinda like, uh, I don't know,

25:06.755 --> 25:09.341
see what it's like to earn
a working-man's wage, you know? Uh...

25:09.424 --> 25:10.884
-[register beeping]
-Oh, I'm sorry.

25:10.967 --> 25:13.386
-I think that's, like, really important.
-Yeah, totally.

25:13.470 --> 25:15.180
Yeah, anyway, this was, like, so fun.

25:15.263 --> 25:17.140
We should kind of like, you know,
I don't know,

25:17.224 --> 25:18.517
maybe hang out this weekend or--

25:18.600 --> 25:20.310
-[coins clatter]
-Oh, sorry about that. Uh...

25:20.393 --> 25:22.145
I don't know. Maybe next weekend or--

25:22.229 --> 25:23.980
Yeah, I'm busy.

25:24.105 --> 25:25.315
Oh, that's cool. I'm--

25:25.398 --> 25:27.108
I'm working here next weekend, so...

25:27.275 --> 25:29.444
the following weekend's better for me.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.488
No. I'm sorry, I can't.

25:31.571 --> 25:33.782
[girl] Okay. Thanks. [chuckles]

25:34.241 --> 25:35.075
I...

25:35.158 --> 25:37.494
-This is... my first day here.
-[girls chuckle]

25:37.577 --> 25:38.662
[sighs]

25:39.663 --> 25:42.040
And another one bites the dust.

25:42.791 --> 25:45.544
You are oh-for-six, Popeye.

25:45.627 --> 25:47.128
Yeah, yeah, I can count.

25:47.212 --> 25:49.005
You know that means you suck.

25:49.089 --> 25:50.549
Yep, I can read, too.

25:50.632 --> 25:51.800
Since when?

25:51.883 --> 25:53.426
It's this stupid hat.

25:53.510 --> 25:56.054
I am telling you,
it is totally blowing my best feature.

25:56.137 --> 25:58.557
Yeah, company policy is a real drag.

25:59.349 --> 26:03.436
You know, it's a crazy idea,
but have you considered...

26:04.104 --> 26:05.021
telling the truth?

26:05.105 --> 26:07.107
Oh, you mean,
that I couldn't even get into Tech

26:07.190 --> 26:09.442
and my douchebag dad's
trying to teach me a lesson,

26:09.526 --> 26:12.279
I make three bucks an hour,
and I have no future? That truth?

26:13.488 --> 26:14.656
Hey, twelve o'clock.

26:15.949 --> 26:18.368
Oh, shit. Oh, shit. Okay... Uh...

26:18.702 --> 26:19.744
I'm going in. Okay?

26:20.829 --> 26:21.830
And you know what?

26:22.622 --> 26:25.542
-Screw company policy.
-Oh, my God, you're a whole new man.

26:25.625 --> 26:27.002
Right? Ooh. [chuckles]

26:27.085 --> 26:29.212
-Ahoy, ladies! Didn't see you there.
-[girl gasps]

26:29.296 --> 26:32.132
Would you guys like to set sail
on this ocean of flavor with me?

26:32.215 --> 26:33.383
I'll be your captain.

26:33.717 --> 26:34.884
I'm Steve Harrington.

26:34.968 --> 26:36.177
-[laughs]
-Oh, God.

26:36.261 --> 26:38.513
Can I get you guys a little taste
of the Cherries Jubilee?

26:38.597 --> 26:40.056
No? Anybody?

26:40.140 --> 26:42.601
Banana Boat? Four people, four spoons?

26:42.684 --> 26:45.145
[Steve] Share it in the booth?
Anybody? It's hot out there.

26:45.729 --> 26:48.231
[Hooper] I know this is
a difficult conversation to have...

26:48.815 --> 26:52.319
but I hope you know that I...
care about you very much.

26:52.819 --> 26:54.779
-And I know that you--
-Eye contact.

26:54.863 --> 26:55.989
[sighs]

26:56.072 --> 26:57.532
["She's Got You" playing]

26:59.075 --> 27:00.285
And I know that you...

27:01.202 --> 27:03.163
both care about each other very much.

27:03.246 --> 27:04.623
This does not sound like me at all.

27:04.706 --> 27:06.583
Just keep going. Come on.

27:08.460 --> 27:12.839
Which is why I think it's important
to establish these boundaries...

27:13.757 --> 27:15.759
moving forward...

27:17.135 --> 27:18.595
No looking. You know this.

27:18.678 --> 27:19.763
-Come on.
-[inhales sharply]

27:20.305 --> 27:22.515
...so we can build an environment...

27:22.766 --> 27:23.933
uh...

27:24.017 --> 27:25.060
where we...

27:25.518 --> 27:27.020
all feel comfortable

27:27.604 --> 27:29.230
and trusted

27:29.981 --> 27:31.107
and open...

27:32.901 --> 27:34.611
"Share our feelings..."

27:34.694 --> 27:37.238
...to sharing our feelings--
This isn't gonna work.

27:37.322 --> 27:39.032
Um, it's not gonna work.
It's not gonna work.

27:39.115 --> 27:41.368
Yes, it will! I promise.

27:41.451 --> 27:42.702
Oh, come on.

27:42.827 --> 27:44.412
Maybe I'll just kill Mike.

27:45.330 --> 27:47.457
I'm the chief of police,
I could cover it up.

27:48.166 --> 27:49.250
You got this.

27:49.334 --> 27:50.251
[Joyce] I promise.

27:50.335 --> 27:54.631
♪ I really don't know what I know ♪

27:54.714 --> 27:56.424
♪ It won't let... ♪

27:56.508 --> 27:57.717
You wanna have dinner tonight?

28:00.303 --> 28:01.805
You can give me some more pointers.

28:01.888 --> 28:03.223
Oh, I... Um...

28:04.224 --> 28:05.684
Um, I...

28:06.685 --> 28:07.811
I have plans.

28:08.770 --> 28:10.355
Okay, sure.

28:13.400 --> 28:14.859
[shop door bell jingles]

28:15.068 --> 28:16.820
Oh, a customer.

28:17.487 --> 28:20.156
-Hey, Carol!
-Oh, hi, Joyce!

28:20.240 --> 28:21.950
How are you? So good to see you.

28:22.033 --> 28:24.703
[Carol] So, um, Georgie has
his 13th birthday coming up.

28:24.786 --> 28:26.496
Oh, my gosh, 13?

28:26.579 --> 28:27.580
I know!

28:27.664 --> 28:29.165
And I'm a little lost...

28:29.249 --> 28:35.463
♪  She's got you  ♪

28:37.257 --> 28:39.259
[panting]

28:40.385 --> 28:41.636
Aren't we high enough?

28:41.845 --> 28:43.763
Cerebro works best at a hundred meters.

28:43.847 --> 28:46.307
You know, I'm pretty sure people in Utah
have telephones.

28:46.391 --> 28:47.726
Yeah, but Suzie's Mormon.

28:47.851 --> 28:49.769
Oh, shit. She doesn't have electricity?

28:49.853 --> 28:50.937
Oh, that's the Amish.

28:51.020 --> 28:53.481
-[Will] What are Mormons?
-Super religious white people.

28:53.732 --> 28:55.900
They have electricity and cars and stuff,
but...

28:56.317 --> 28:58.778
since I'm not Mormon,
her parents would never approve.

29:00.196 --> 29:01.156
It's all a bit...

29:02.115 --> 29:03.158
Shakespearean.

29:03.241 --> 29:04.284
Shakespearean?

29:04.909 --> 29:07.287
Yeah. Like  Romeo and Juliet.

29:07.370 --> 29:08.204
Right.

29:08.705 --> 29:10.123
-Star-crossed lovers.
-I got it.

29:10.206 --> 29:11.166
Hey, guys!

29:12.876 --> 29:14.377
[Mike] This is fun and all, but, uh...

29:14.961 --> 29:15.837
I have to go home.

29:15.920 --> 29:17.547
-We're almost there.
-[Mike] Sorry, man.

29:17.630 --> 29:18.506
Curfew.

29:18.882 --> 29:20.675
-Come on, let's go.
-Good luck.

29:21.426 --> 29:22.552
[Eleven giggles]

29:23.636 --> 29:25.680
-Curfew at 4:00?
-They're lying.

29:25.764 --> 29:27.682
-It's been like this all summer.
-It's romantic.

29:27.766 --> 29:29.684
-It's gross.
-It's bullshit.

29:30.351 --> 29:31.436
I just got home.

29:33.730 --> 29:35.023
[Dustin] Well, their loss, right?

29:35.732 --> 29:37.025
Onwards and upwards!

29:37.108 --> 29:38.651
-Suzie awaits!
-[both sigh]

29:46.326 --> 29:49.120
[fluttering sound]

29:55.543 --> 29:56.628
[Dustin] Will, come on!

30:00.173 --> 30:02.091
[squealing]

30:13.728 --> 30:15.730
[squealing]

30:32.705 --> 30:34.707
[frantic squealing]

30:35.041 --> 30:36.084
[screeching]

30:37.418 --> 30:40.088
[all screeching]

30:50.515 --> 30:52.517
["Hot Blooded" playing]

30:56.896 --> 30:58.189
♪ Well I'm ♪

30:58.273 --> 30:59.816
♪ Hot blooded ♪

30:59.899 --> 31:01.484
♪ Check it and see ♪

31:02.318 --> 31:03.361
♪ I've got a fever ♪

31:03.444 --> 31:05.488
♪ Of a hundred and three ♪

31:06.322 --> 31:07.282
♪ Come on baby ♪

31:07.365 --> 31:09.576
♪ Do you do more than dance? ♪

31:10.201 --> 31:12.996
♪ I'm hot blooded, I'm hot blooded... ♪

31:13.079 --> 31:15.248
[whistle blowing]

31:16.291 --> 31:17.667
[crowd screaming and laughing]

31:25.592 --> 31:27.468
Looking good out there, Mrs. Wheeler.

31:28.136 --> 31:29.596
[sighs] Thank you.

31:29.679 --> 31:30.847
Perfect form.

31:31.806 --> 31:32.682
Well...

31:33.433 --> 31:34.559
your form is amazing.

31:35.143 --> 31:35.977
[chuckles]

31:36.060 --> 31:37.228
I'm sorry, I mean, I...

31:38.021 --> 31:40.648
I've seen you... uh, teaching...

31:40.732 --> 31:41.608
[chuckles]

31:41.691 --> 31:43.318
...lessons. Swimming lessons.

31:44.277 --> 31:45.945
You know, I could, uh...

31:46.696 --> 31:48.239
I could teach you, if you like.

31:48.323 --> 31:49.282
Oh.

31:49.365 --> 31:50.533
I know all the styles.

31:50.992 --> 31:52.160
Freestyle.

31:53.202 --> 31:54.078
Butterfly.

31:57.040 --> 31:58.374
Breaststroke.

32:00.335 --> 32:01.419
-Oh.
-Oh!

32:01.711 --> 32:02.545
You okay?

32:04.005 --> 32:06.716
I didn't think you...
I didn't think you taught adults.

32:06.799 --> 32:08.384
Well, I offer more, uh...

32:09.594 --> 32:13.139
advanced lessons to select clientele.

32:13.222 --> 32:14.057
Oh.

32:14.140 --> 32:17.018
Come to think of it, there is a good pool

32:17.268 --> 32:20.480
out at a Motel 6 on Cornwallis.

32:20.563 --> 32:21.981
It's very quiet.

32:23.191 --> 32:24.734
You know, very private.

32:24.817 --> 32:25.735
Mm.

32:27.320 --> 32:28.613
Shall we say tonight?

32:29.697 --> 32:30.782
Eight o'clock?

32:34.118 --> 32:35.036
I'm sorry.

32:35.578 --> 32:36.412
I can't.

32:36.496 --> 32:37.956
Can't what? Have fun?

32:38.039 --> 32:39.374
[laughs]

32:39.457 --> 32:41.167
-Mrs. Wheeler!
-No.

32:42.418 --> 32:45.797
I... I... I just, uh...
I don't think I need any lessons.

32:46.214 --> 32:47.840
Oh, you see, I think you do.

32:48.508 --> 32:51.219
I just don't think
that you've had the right teacher.

32:51.302 --> 32:53.846
-I, uh...
-It will be

32:53.930 --> 32:56.349
the workout of your life.

33:04.524 --> 33:05.400
Made it.

33:05.817 --> 33:07.694
Yeah, only took five hours.

33:07.819 --> 33:09.612
Why couldn't we just play D&D?

33:10.113 --> 33:11.280
I'm so thirsty.

33:15.618 --> 33:17.787
[gulping loudly]

33:24.085 --> 33:26.129
Did you seriously just drink
the rest of our water?

33:59.037 --> 34:00.413
Pretty impressive, right?

34:00.830 --> 34:02.665
-Yeah.
-Now, you ready to meet my love?

34:02.749 --> 34:04.042
-[Max] Okay, sure.
-[Will] Yeah.

34:04.834 --> 34:06.002
[radio switches on]

34:07.628 --> 34:10.798
Suzie, this is Dustin. Do you copy? Over.

34:10.882 --> 34:12.884
[radio static hissing]

34:15.595 --> 34:17.764
One sec. She's probably...
She's still there.

34:17.847 --> 34:18.723
Suzie...

34:19.640 --> 34:21.642
this is Dustin. Do you copy? Over.

34:21.726 --> 34:23.269
[radio static hissing]

34:25.938 --> 34:27.690
I'm sure she's there. It's just--

34:27.815 --> 34:29.859
-[Lucas] Yeah.
-You know, maybe she's, like, busy or--

34:29.942 --> 34:31.694
-Yeah.
-[Dustin] It's around dinnertime.

34:31.778 --> 34:32.653
-Mmm.
-Yep.

34:32.737 --> 34:33.821
Here.

34:36.115 --> 34:39.118
Suzie, do you copy? This is Dustin. Over.

34:39.202 --> 34:41.204
[radio static hissing]

34:43.456 --> 34:46.793
Suzie, do you copy? This is Dustin. Over.

34:46.876 --> 34:48.878
[radio static hissing]

34:59.180 --> 35:00.640
Hey, guys, I'm home.

35:03.351 --> 35:04.268
Guys?

35:07.188 --> 35:08.106
Hello?

35:28.084 --> 35:29.252
[TV switches on]

35:29.669 --> 35:32.380
-[woman speaking indistinctly on TV]
- [audience laughter]

35:32.463 --> 35:33.381
[man on TV]  Ah!

35:33.464 --> 35:35.174
So, who do you wanna speak to next?

35:35.258 --> 35:37.260
[audience laughter]

35:37.635 --> 35:39.303
[woman]  I'm talking about Frasier, Sam.

35:39.804 --> 35:43.432
He had a couple of sips of Chianti tonight
and asked me to marry him.

35:43.516 --> 35:44.725
[TV audio echoes]

35:45.059 --> 35:47.145
[Sam]  Did you say a couple of sips,
or barrels?

35:47.228 --> 35:49.105
[sound of Bob's laughter]

35:49.188 --> 35:50.690
[both laughing]

35:50.982 --> 35:52.316
Ahh!

35:52.400 --> 35:55.862
-Ah, they're funny, don't you think?
-Yes.

35:56.863 --> 35:59.407
I just wish they'd
get back together again already.

35:59.615 --> 36:00.449
Me too.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.660
[woman]  You don't think that I still--

36:02.743 --> 36:04.495
-Well, of course I--
-[Sam]  You bet your--

36:04.579 --> 36:05.454
[laughing]

36:05.538 --> 36:07.165
[laughs]

36:08.708 --> 36:11.752
[woman]  Tell everyone that I'll call
after the wedding tomorrow.

36:13.921 --> 36:15.381
[Sam]  Tomorrow? What's the rush?

36:16.966 --> 36:19.177
[woman] Frasi er has thoughtfully
and romantically

36:19.260 --> 36:21.345
arranged for us to be married

36:21.429 --> 36:22.889
at the Marino estate.

36:23.347 --> 36:24.891
[TV audio fades]

36:24.974 --> 36:26.976
[eerie music playing]

36:32.315 --> 36:34.609
[fridge magnet rattles]

36:45.912 --> 36:47.955
[phone ringing]

36:52.126 --> 36:53.711
[Nancy whispers] Shit, shit.

36:54.670 --> 36:55.755
Hawkins Post.

36:55.838 --> 36:57.840
[indistinct female voice on line]

36:58.716 --> 37:00.218
Um, hold on, I'm--

37:00.301 --> 37:02.511
I'm sorry, can you-- can you repeat that?

37:13.522 --> 37:18.778
["Can't Fight This Feeling" playing]
♪ ...than I ever thought I might ♪

37:20.404 --> 37:24.784
♪ And I can't fight this feeling
Anymore ...  ♪

37:25.868 --> 37:26.911
[song continues]

37:26.994 --> 37:30.206
...why it's important
to establish these boundaries...

37:31.832 --> 37:36.212
moving forward, so that we can
create an environment where...

37:38.172 --> 37:41.008
you feel comfortable and trusted
and open.

37:44.303 --> 37:45.888
Shit.

37:48.432 --> 37:50.810
"To share our feelings."

37:56.983 --> 37:58.609
[exhales sharply, grunts]

38:12.748 --> 38:13.708
Hey.

38:15.293 --> 38:16.168
[Eleven] Yes?

38:17.086 --> 38:18.713
Can I talk to you guys a minute?

38:21.716 --> 38:23.718
[song continues]

38:29.265 --> 38:30.099
Hi.

38:31.183 --> 38:32.143
[both] Hi.

38:32.393 --> 38:36.856
♪ My life has been such a whirlwind
Since I saw you ♪

38:38.691 --> 38:42.737
♪ I've been running around in circles
In my mind ♪

38:44.739 --> 38:50.369
♪ And it always seems
That I'm following you, girl ♪

38:51.037 --> 38:53.331
♪ 'Cause you take me to the places ♪

38:53.914 --> 38:55.833
♪That alone I'd never fi-- ♪

38:55.916 --> 38:56.834
[stereo switches off]

39:05.801 --> 39:06.677
Um...

39:15.770 --> 39:16.979
What I, uh...

39:20.524 --> 39:22.443
needed to say to you...

39:25.321 --> 39:26.697
What I wanted

39:27.490 --> 39:28.657
to say to you...

39:29.867 --> 39:30.701
is that, um...

39:31.285 --> 39:32.286
Uh-oh.

39:33.245 --> 39:34.497
I think we're in trouble.

39:36.040 --> 39:37.750
[both chuckling]

39:38.334 --> 39:39.460
[both chuckling]

39:42.463 --> 39:43.297
No.

39:45.299 --> 39:46.842
No, nobody's in trouble, okay?

39:46.926 --> 39:48.302
I just, um...

39:49.470 --> 39:50.304
[Hopper] Uh...

39:50.888 --> 39:53.015
[Eleven laughs]

39:56.018 --> 39:57.019
You know what?

39:57.645 --> 39:58.813
Your mom called.

40:00.564 --> 40:01.482
What?

40:02.441 --> 40:03.359
Yeah.

40:03.818 --> 40:05.611
She needs you home right away.

40:05.694 --> 40:07.446
Is everything okay?

40:07.530 --> 40:08.656
No, I don't think so.

40:09.365 --> 40:10.533
It's your grandma.

40:14.161 --> 40:15.454
-Is she dead?
-No.

40:15.538 --> 40:16.914
-Did she fall again?
-No.

40:16.997 --> 40:18.332
Does she have cancer?

40:18.999 --> 40:20.835
-No.
-Then I don't understand.

40:20.918 --> 40:22.336
What's wrong with Nana?

40:23.671 --> 40:26.465
Nothing! There's nothing wrong with Nana!

40:27.049 --> 40:28.384
-What?
-But...

40:28.968 --> 40:33.681
there's something very wrong
with this thing between you and El.

40:33.764 --> 40:34.890
[sniffles, grunts]

40:36.183 --> 40:37.810
Oh, you lying piece of shit!

40:43.816 --> 40:44.859
You're crazy!

40:44.942 --> 40:46.026
Crazy?

40:47.945 --> 40:49.697
You want to see real crazy?

40:50.865 --> 40:52.533
You disrespect me again.

40:54.535 --> 40:55.369
Okay?

40:58.080 --> 40:59.707
Here's what's gonna happen.

41:01.167 --> 41:02.626
I'm gonna drive you home.

41:04.295 --> 41:07.047
And I'm gonna speak...

41:08.132 --> 41:11.510
and you're going to listen.

41:12.970 --> 41:14.555
And then, maybe...

41:15.973 --> 41:18.976
maybe by the end of it,
maybe if you're lucky, maybe...

41:19.977 --> 41:21.687
I will continue

41:22.813 --> 41:27.651
to allow you to date my daughter.

41:32.323 --> 41:35.576
Nod if you understand!

41:35.659 --> 41:36.577
[engine starts]

41:39.872 --> 41:42.333
...do you copy? This is Dustin. Over.

41:42.416 --> 41:44.168
[radio static hissing]

41:46.212 --> 41:49.840
Suzie! This is Dustin. Do you copy? Over.

41:49.924 --> 41:51.675
[radio static hissing]

41:52.551 --> 41:56.055
Suzie, this is your Dustin.
Do you copy? Over.

41:56.138 --> 41:57.306
[radio static hissing]

41:57.598 --> 42:00.226
-Suzie--
-Dustin, come on! She's not there.

42:00.309 --> 42:01.810
She's there, all right? She'll pick up.

42:01.894 --> 42:05.564
-Maybe Cerebro doesn't work.
-Or maybe Suzie doesn't exist.

42:05.648 --> 42:06.565
She exists!

42:06.649 --> 42:08.984
She's a genius
and  she's hotter than Phoebe Cates?

42:09.568 --> 42:11.362
No girl is that perfect.

42:11.946 --> 42:12.821
Is that so?

42:14.490 --> 42:15.366
I mean...

42:15.741 --> 42:16.825
you're perfect.

42:16.909 --> 42:19.787
[stammers] I mean, like, per-- perfect
in your own way.

42:19.870 --> 42:21.622
In your special-- your own special way.

42:22.331 --> 42:23.165
[chuckles]

42:23.249 --> 42:24.458
Relax, I was teasing.

42:25.125 --> 42:28.754
I'm obviously perfect
and Dustin's obviously lying.

42:29.255 --> 42:30.506
[Max] Come on, Don Juan.

42:32.174 --> 42:33.842
-Where are you going?
-[Max] Home.

42:35.594 --> 42:38.514
Well... guess it's just you and me, Byers.

42:39.139 --> 42:41.392
Um... it's late.

42:42.268 --> 42:43.227
Sorry.

42:43.686 --> 42:45.813
Maybe tomorrow we can play D&D.

42:46.188 --> 42:48.023
Or something fun. Like we used to?

42:49.066 --> 42:50.025
Yeah, sure.

42:50.985 --> 42:51.944
Welcome home.

42:59.827 --> 43:00.661
Yeah.

43:01.287 --> 43:02.246
Welcome home.

43:03.247 --> 43:05.291
[distorted radio chatter]

43:05.374 --> 43:06.584
Shit.

43:07.918 --> 43:08.752
Shit.

43:09.962 --> 43:12.131
Suzie? Suzie, is that you?

43:12.214 --> 43:15.050
[man speaking Russian over radio]

43:16.885 --> 43:18.137
[volume increases]

43:18.220 --> 43:20.222
[male voice continues]

43:22.224 --> 43:24.101
[in Russian] The silver cat feeds--

43:24.476 --> 43:27.146
when blue meets yellow in the west--

43:28.188 --> 43:33.736
A trip to China sounds nice--
If you tread lightly--

43:34.403 --> 43:35.904
The week is long--

43:36.530 --> 43:38.240
The silver cat feeds--

43:56.050 --> 43:56.967
[in Russian] Beautiful,

43:58.093 --> 43:59.094
isn't it?

44:13.150 --> 44:15.069
["(I Just) Died in Your Arms" playing]

44:21.158 --> 44:24.620
♪ I keep looking for something
I can't get ♪

44:25.204 --> 44:27.956
♪ Broken hearts lie all around me ♪

44:28.040 --> 44:33.170
♪ And I don't see an easy way
To get out of this ♪

44:36.006 --> 44:39.885
♪ Her diary sits by the bedside table ♪

44:39.968 --> 44:43.597
♪ The curtains are closed
The cat's in the cradle ♪

44:43.681 --> 44:47.351
♪ Who would've thought
That a boy like me ♪

44:47.434 --> 44:49.061
♪ Could come to this? ♪

44:49.895 --> 44:52.439
♪ Oh, oh, I ♪

44:52.773 --> 44:55.943
♪ I just died in your arms tonight ♪

44:56.026 --> 44:57.152
[snoring]

44:57.236 --> 45:00.030
♪ It must've been something you said ♪

45:00.489 --> 45:03.909
♪ I just died in your arms tonight ♪

45:04.868 --> 45:08.163
♪ It must've been some kind of kiss ♪

45:08.580 --> 45:12.459
-♪ I should've walked away ♪
-[Ted snoring]

45:12.960 --> 45:15.963
♪ I should've walked away ♪

45:20.092 --> 45:22.094
[heavy metal playing on car stereo]

45:28.892 --> 45:30.894
[laughs]

45:35.691 --> 45:36.567
Hey, Karen.

45:39.194 --> 45:41.071
You don't mind if I call you Karen,
do you?

45:42.614 --> 45:43.449
Good.

45:44.032 --> 45:45.576
[tires screeching]

45:49.455 --> 45:50.622
[grunts]

45:51.206 --> 45:52.374
[groans]

45:54.877 --> 45:56.253
Oh, no.

45:56.712 --> 45:59.047
No. Piece of shit.

45:59.131 --> 46:00.799
[song resumes with distortion]

46:00.883 --> 46:01.884
Shit.

46:02.885 --> 46:03.927
Damn it!

46:05.053 --> 46:06.305
[grunts]

46:09.433 --> 46:11.101
[owl hooting]

46:13.687 --> 46:14.730
Ah, shit.

46:17.441 --> 46:18.317
Damn it!

46:19.860 --> 46:21.195
Piece of shit!

46:26.450 --> 46:28.243
[steam hissing]

46:32.998 --> 46:33.832
[wet squelching]

46:36.210 --> 46:37.419
What the hell?

46:37.503 --> 46:38.670
[creature shrieks]

46:43.425 --> 46:44.510
Who's there?

46:48.096 --> 46:49.014
Hey!

46:50.849 --> 46:51.892
I said, who's there?

46:52.434 --> 46:53.769
[yells, grunts]

46:54.228 --> 46:56.146
[screaming]

47:00.067 --> 47:02.194
[screaming]

47:03.570 --> 47:05.280
[grunts, yells]

47:06.406 --> 47:08.867
[screams]

47:09.159 --> 47:10.953
[creature shrieking distantly]

47:11.203 --> 47:13.580
[growling, wailing]

47:17.417 --> 47:18.877
[theme music playing]

49:01.271 --> 49:02.314
[monkey screeching]
